%p
  A 'division' is parliamentary terminology for a 'vote'
  (#{link_to "read more...", "/faq.php#jargon"}).
  This page shows divisions in the Australian parliament. Make sure you
  = link_to "read the explanation", "/faq.php#clarify"
  about rebellions, as they may not be what you expect.

%p{:align => "center", :style => "font-size: 89%"}
  Sort by:
  %b Date
  |
  = link_to "Subject", "divisions.php?sort=subject", alt: "Sort by subject"
  |
  = link_to "Rebellions", "divisions.php?sort=rebellions", alt: "Sort by rebellions"
  |
  = link_to "Turnout", "divisions.php?sort=turnout", alt: "Sort by turnout"
  %table.votes
    %tr.headings
      %td House
      %td Date
      %td Time
      %td Subject
      %td
        Rebels
        %br>/
        (#{link_to "explain..", "/faq.php#clarify"})
      %td Turnout
      %td Majority
    - @divisions.each do |division|
      %tr{:class => cycle("even", "odd")}
        %td{:class => division.house}= division.australian_house_name
        %td= division.date.strftime("%d&nbsp;%b&nbsp;%Y").html_safe
        %td
          - if division.clock_time
            = division.clock_time.strftime("%H:%M")
        %td
          = link_to division.name, "division.php?date=#{division.date}&number=#{division.number}&house=#{division.australian_house}"
        %td= division.rebellions
        %td= division.turnout
        %td= division.majority
